SEARS, ROEBUCK & CO., a Corporation, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Carter H. HARRISON, Individually and as Collector of Internal Revenue for the First Collection District of Illinois, Defendant-Appellee. No. 6546. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. March 23, 1938. Charles Lederer, Sigmund Livingston, and Bert L. Klooster, all of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. M. L. Igoe, U. S. Atty., of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On'motion of counsel for appellant, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
